  • Method Details

    • makeDisplayed

      public void makeDisplayed()
      Sets the display state to active, initializes the Shuffleboard tab and layout for displaying values. Configures the layout size and position based on the provided column.

    • registerListener

      public void registerListener(Runnable listener)
      Registers a listener to the display values helper. Listeners will be called when the notifyListeners function is called. This function is used to update the display values on the dashboard.
      Parameters:
      listener - - Runnable to be called when notifyListeners is called

    • unregisterListener

      public void unregisterListener(Runnable listener)
      Removes a listener from the display values helper. This listener will not be called when notifyListeners is called.
      Parameters:
      listener - - Runnable to be removed from the list of listeners

    • notifyListeners

      public void notifyListeners()
      Calls all registered listeners. This should be called when a value is updated so that all dashboard values are updated.

    • display

      public void display(String key, Supplier<String> value)
      Registers a value to be displayed on the dashboard. The value will be retrieved by calling the provided Supplier, and the result will be displayed on the dashboard when the notifyListeners function is called.
      Parameters:
      key - the name of the value to be displayed
      value - a Supplier that returns the value to be displayed

    • display

      public void display(String key, edu.wpi.first.util.sendable.Sendable value)

    • setLoggingLevel

      public void setLoggingLevel(GenericRobot.LogLevel level)
      Sets the logging level for the display. Values that are at a higher or equal level to the specified level will be displayed on the dashboard.
      Parameters:
      level - the level to set the display to

    • getLoggingLevel

      Returns:
      true if the robot's current log level is at or above the specified level, false otherwise
